              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Vermeer</td>
                <td>$2,550</td>
                <td>$1,150</td>
                <td><strong>$1,400</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Morbark</td>
                <td>$7,200</td>
                <td>$3,500</td>
                <td><strong>$3,700</strong></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <aside class="nesh-cc-savings-callout" aria-label="Maximum savings">
          <strong>$3,700</strong>
          <span>Maximum listed savings versus new replacement pricing</span>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="nesh-cc-section">
      <h2>Why rebuild instead of waiting on a new assembly?</h2>
      <div class="nesh-cc-grid">
        <article class="nesh-cc-card"><h3>Lower replacement cost</h3><p>A rebuild can help avoid new-part pricing when the converter shell is reusable and the internal components can be restored.</p></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-card"><h3>Less downtime pressure</h3><p>Tree service and land-clearing crews depend on working chippers. A rebuild gives you a practical path when sourcing new components slows the repair.</p></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-card"><h3>Handled by a parts supplier</h3><p>New England Supply House supports equipment owners and repair shops with parts sourcing, rebuild coordination, and order support.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="nesh-cc-section">
      <h2>How the rebuild works</h2>
      <div class="nesh-cc-steps">
        <article class="nesh-cc-step"><h3>Order online</h3><p>Choose the D&S Bandit, Morbark, or Vermeer rebuild option.</p></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-step"><h3>Send your core</h3><p>New England Supply House sends instructions for shipping your existing converter.</p></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-step"><h3>Inspection and rebuild</h3><p>The unit is inspected and damaged internal components are rebuilt.</p></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-step"><h3>Return and install</h3><p>Your rebuilt converter is returned for installation on compatible equipment.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="nesh-cc-section">
      <div class="nesh-cc-grid">
        <article class="nesh-cc-card"><h3>Available options</h3><ul><li>D&S Bandit rebuild</li><li>D&S Morbark rebuild</li><li>D&S Vermeer rebuild</li></ul></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-card"><h3>Good fit for</h3><ul><li>Tree service companies</li><li>Wood chipper repair shops</li><li>Land clearing contractors</li><li>Equipment fleets</li></ul></article>
        <article class="nesh-cc-card"><h3>Questions before ordering?</h3><p>Call New England Supply House at <a href="tel:17747016374">774-701-6374</a> or review the product page for current stock and checkout options.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="nesh-cc-section">
      <div class="nesh-cc-final">
        <h2>Ready to get your chipper back to work?</h2>
        <p>Order the rebuild online, then send your existing D&S converter core using the instructions provided after purchase.</p>
        <div class="nesh-cc-actions">
          <a class="nesh-cc-button" href="/products/replacement-catalytic-converter-bandit-vermeer-morbark">Order the rebuild</a>
          <a class="nesh-cc-button secondary" href="tel:17747016374">Call 774-701-6374</a>
        </div>
        <div class="nesh-cc-note">Confirm fitment and applicable emissions requirements before ordering. Typical turnaround is 1-2 weeks after your converter core is received.</div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</section>

